body:
For a struct with a field of integer value, Unmarshal() doesn't put the value in the field. The value is always 0.  Example code:
-------------
package	main
import (
        "fmt"
        "encoding/json"
)
type Animal struct {
	name  string
	order int
}
func main() {
     var jsonBlob = []byte(`
                  {"name": "Platypus", "order": 10}
                                  `)
                     var one Animal
                     var err = json.Unmarshal(jsonBlob, &one)
				if err != nil {
                                         fmt.Println("error:", err)
                           }
                     fmt.Printf("One:%+v", one)
}
----------
The order field is of value 0 which should be 10. If the field name is changed to "Order", then it works.
